{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"408cc1a8-f669-4a6b-83ac-21bca7984c5f","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** In xUnit, `Skip` is a property on the test attribute itself rather than a separate attribute. All four frameworks will report skipped tests distinctly from passes/failures in test results.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3df6701f-f7fb-4337-99d1-8ba109e3a074","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":328,"requestId":"7034:358C2B:ADB066:C99661:69F2AC3F"},"id":"da0da8cf-7d00-4052-8df4-b4bb06b31c97","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:11:34.222Z","parentId":"14edcf97-0c48-46d4-8e04-912ba92db5f2"}
